<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">&nbsp;{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="4"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div>
<p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span class="s1">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Welcome back to the start of our final term. We hope you have all had an enjoyable and restful Easter break. Ahead of us, we have another exciting term with the Year 4 production of Hoodwinked, Robotics and many interesting topics for the children to learn about.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><br></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" color="#3366ff"><b>English</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In their English lessons, the children will be learning about and composing different types of texts including Persuasive Speeches, Fractured Fairy Tales and various types of non-fiction writing to inform a specific audience. They will be reading and identifying the features of persuasive speeches before writing and presenting their own versions. They will also be reading a variety of fractured fairy tales, including ‘<i>The True Story of the Three Little Pigs</i>’ before planning and writing their own exciting texts. Continuing from Term 1 and 2, the children will have lessons in Spelling, Punctuation and Grammar (SPaG); these will be an integral part of the daily English lessons. They will also participate in regular guided reading sessions.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Mathematics</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In their maths lessons, the children will continue to use the new <i>Mathematics Mastery</i> approach to ensure that they achieve a deep understanding of the concepts they are learning. This term, they will learn about various aspects of geometry, including angles, shape and symmetry, position and direction. Following their study of geometry, the children will spend time learning about statistics, including interpreting and creating their own graphs. To conclude Term 3, they will consolidate and apply their knowledge of whole number and decimals. Problem Solving will be embedded into all areas of maths curriculum. To improve their mathematical fluency, the children will also be aiming to improve their knowledge of time tables and corresponding division facts through the weekly Ninja Challenge.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Science</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Our science topic this term is <i>Electricity</i>. Within this unit, children will research which products run on electricity, study the impact of electricity on our lives, then investigate and construct simple series electrical circuits, identifying and naming basic parts. They will apply their understanding of electrical circuits to create their own electric steady-hand testing game. Investigations, as well as the acquisition of knowledge, will be a key part in the learning process.&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Computing</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">After two terms, the children are now becoming familiar with their iPads and the various apps they are using across the curriculum. This term, children will continue learning how to code and also learn about robotics, which links very nicely with our Electricity topic in science.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Integrated Curriculum (Topic)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Our topic this term is <b>Stone Age to Iron Age</b>. Where possible there will be cross curricular links between the topic and English. During their topic lessons, the children will research what happened in the Stone Age, compare and contrast homes from Palaeolithic, Mesolithic and Neolithic times. They will also investigate how life changed during the Bronze and Iron Ages, and compare and contrast life in the Stone Age with life today. In their art lessons, the children will create pictures in the style of cave paintings, design and make their own Stone Age houses.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Modern Foreign Languages (MFL)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Spanish&nbsp;</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">The Year 4 Spanish group will be covering a number of short topics this term including:- <i>Pets, Wild Animals and their Habitats, My Face and Body, Hobbies and Sports and Clothes</i>. The children will be learning through creative activities, games, songs and stories. They will be encouraged to give their opinions and say what they like and dislike to develop their fluency and confidence. The topics will also enable the children to develop their grammar and use of verbs and adjectives. The children will also be preparing to perform in the Spanish assembly in the third term.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Mandarin</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In term 3, the Mandarin lessons for beginner level will cover the topics of <i>“Animals”, “Colours”, “Adjectives and Body Parts”</i> and <i>“Countries and Languages”</i>. Children in Elementary level will cover the topics of “Weather”, “School timetables” and “Stationery”. The Heritage group will focus on the passage “<i>Xiao Niao Hui Chang Ge</i>” (Little Bird is Able to Sing) , “<i>Wo Men Yao Qu Pa Shan</i>” (We are Going Hiking in the Mountain) and “<i>Wo Ke Yi Kan Dian Shi Ma?</i>” (Can I Watch TV?), “<i>Xiao Ling De Jia Zai Tang Ren Jie Fu Jin</i>” (Xiao Ling’s House is Nearby the China town).&nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">All levels will continue to develop children's listening, speaking, reading and writing skills.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Music</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Hoodwinked: Production</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">The children will be working extensively on their production of '<i>Hoodwinked</i>'. In music they will work as a chorus, focusing primarily on singing. They will develop their skills in projection and performing with confidence.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="font-size: 12pt;">Painting with Sound: Exploring Sound Colours</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">The children will develop their understanding of the link between music and how it can create images and represent stories. They will work in groups to create soundscapes to advertise a product.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Physical Education (PE)</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">In their PE lessons, the Year 4 children will take part in some of the following activities: &nbsp;tag rugby, athletics, striking and fielding games, unihoc, badminton, dance, games making, gymnastics and OAA (Outdoor and Adventurous Activities). &nbsp;These activities will be rotated throughout the term, so that by the end of Term 3, all groups will have completed all the PE activities on the Year 4 PE curriculum, across the academic year. &nbsp;</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Homework</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Each week, children will be given two pieces of homework: one piece will be English/topic related and the other will be mathematics. All children at BSKL are encouraged to read daily, this will need to be recorded in the <i>Reading Record</i>. The children will also need to continue practising times tables and corresponding division facts. In addition, children will receive a weekly homework activity from their Mandarin or Spanish teacher.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Communication</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Each Year 4 class will continue to share with you what is happening in class via the class portal blogs. Any changes to normal school routine or important dates/events will be shared via the school calendar. Although a notification e-mail may be sent, we encourage parents to check the Parent Portal calendar regularly.</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">For safeguarding purposes, can we ask that adults wear their identification tags at all times within school and if your child is due to be collected by someone else, please do inform us in advance.</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><b style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255); font-size: 12pt;">Events to look forward to this term:</b></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">29th April<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Open Morning</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">4th May <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Year 5 sports day</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">20th May<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>5C Class assembly</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">1st June<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Pupil led conferences</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">21st June <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">		</span>Year 4 production of ‘<i>Hoodwinked</i>’</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">1st July<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>International Day (children to dress up)</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">12th July<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">			</span>Hari Raya Celebration Day (children to dress up)</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">I hope this letter gives you a brief insight into what your child will be learning this term. As always, if you have any questions or concerns please contact your class teacher as a first point of contact.&nbsp;</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Kind regards,</span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Year 4 Team</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Carol Comber (Year Group Leader)&nbsp;</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">carol.comber@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Simon Clarke &nbsp;</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">simon.clarke@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Gemma Taylor</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">gemma.taylor@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>John Bradshaw</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">john.bradshaw@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial"><b>Chloe Tabley</b></font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">chloe.tabley@britishschool.edu.my</font></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">Teaching Assistants (Mr Jason, Ms Katie, Mr Noel, Ms Thomas &amp; Ms Sinead)</font></p><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><p class="p2" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span class="s1"></span></p><p class="p1" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span class="s1"><br></span></p></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
